      • executeTest

        void executeTest(java.lang.String testRunUri,
                 TestRecord[] testRecords)
          throws java.rmi.RemoteException
        Executes Test Cases given by the Test Records within a specified Test Run. This method differs from others within this web service because it can execute multiple Test Cases in a single call. It can also create a defect if a Test Case fails. (If configured to do so on the Polarion server.) It replaces having to call multiple web services like addTestRecord(...) or updateTestRecord(...) and the manual creation of a defect. Test parameters in the supplied test records override any parameters contained within the original planned test records and the test run itself. If a required parameter is supplied with an empty value, the method will fail. It is not necessary to fill all the parameters, only those you want to fill at this moment - only those that do not have a value set in the test run or planned test case, or those that you want to change.
        Parameters:
        testRunUri - the URI of the Test Run (not null)
        testRecords - an array containing Test Records for executed Test Cases. Submitted Test Records are automatically updated (e.g. when a Test Case is planned, paused) or created. (not null)
        Throws:
        java.rmi.RemoteException
        Since:
        3.10.3

               throws java.rmi.RemoteException
        Update a test record.
        Parameters:
        testRunUri - URI of the test run in which the test record will be updated.

        testResultId - ID of the test result, can be null.
        testComment - comment to be tracked with the test record, can be null.
        executedByUri - URI of the user to be used as author of the test record, can be null.
        executed - date when the test case has been executed, can be null.
